race.comment: NYMPHADORA (7) comes out of a solid rating race after pushing forward from the inside gate and holding on for a narrow third over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Should be at her top and can pounce late. MISSIE LEE (8) slow into stride and was giving them a big start when a battling third over 1200m at Wyong. Gets weight relief today with the linkers being applied. Sure to be thereabouts. SPICE BABY (11) Tassort filly resuming. Gave them a galloping lesson on debut in weaker company when saluting over 1020m at Moruya as fav. Fitted with the one trial placing over 780m at Kembla Grange. Looks up to this. Keep safe. DIVO (1) speedy gelding resuming after showing ability in his two-year-old season. Returns with the two trials and has the speed to overcome the sticky draw.
